### AuthService HTTP tests
# Set `baseUrl` to the running AuthService URL. Default for local `dotnet run` is http://localhost:5019
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5177
@TENANT_ID =  # Capture TenantId from Register response here
@ACCESS_TOKEN =  # Capture AccessToken from Login response here

### Register Tenant (creates tenant + admin user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tenantName": "Acme Inc",
  "slug": "acme",
  "adminEmail": "admin@acme.test",
  "adminPassword": "Password123!"
}

### Login (returns AccessToken and RefreshToken)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@acme.test",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "tenantSlug": "acme"
}

### Create API Key (requires Bearer token returned from Login)
### Replace {{ACCESS_TOKEN}} with the `AccessToken` value from Login response.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/tenants/{{TENANT_ID}}/keys
Authorization: Bearer {{ACCESS_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Postman key"
}

### Get Tenant (simple) — replace {id}
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/tenants/{{TENANT_ID}}

### Notes
- After `register`, capture `TenantId` and `AccessToken` from the response.
- Use `TenantId` as `{{TENANT_ID}}` for subsequent requests.
- If running in Docker compose, set `@baseUrl = http://localhost:8082` instead.